Brad Dickson for The New York Times
Reported by Anne Mancuso and Lisa Prevost
Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York and Connecticut.
• In Bronxville, N.Y., a four-bedroom, three-and-a-half-bath 1929 house with original stained glass and wood details, two wood-burning fireplaces, a finished lower level with two wall murals dating to the World War II era, and a two-story addition with family room, bedroom with a full bath, on 0.17 acres on a cul-de-sac
• In Fairfield, Conn., a three-bedroom, two-bath house with ebony-stained oak floors, living room with marble fireplace, open kitchen and dining area, finished lower level with access to yard, central air-conditioning, back deck, and one-car attached garage on 0.17 acres in the Stratfield section of Fairfield.
